ed wallet is Keplr)\\nupon app launching and when the user connects to a new wallet.</p><p>This will update the user&#x27;s compliance status based on the requesting IP.  To authenticate the user, sign a message with the user&#x27;s private key, and send the signed message as part of the payload. See <a href=\\\"https://github.com/dydxprotocol/v4-web/blob/main/src/bonsai/rest/compliance.ts#L158\\\">sample</a> implementation.</p></div><div data-depth=\\\"3\\\">\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/interaction/integration/integration-compliance.mdx#v4geo\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"Third parties are expected to implement geo-blocking themselves but can rely on location information provided by the indexer’s /v4/geo endpoint:curl https://api.dydx.exchange/v4/geo\\n \\n{&quot;geo&quot;:{&quot;country&quot;:&quot;JP&quot;,&quot;region&quot;:&quot;Tokyo&quot;,&quot;regionCode&quot;:&quot;13&quot;,&quot;city&quot;:&quot;Tokyo&quot;,&quot;timezone&quot;:&quot;Asia/Tokyo&quot;,&quot;ll&quot;:[35.6164,139.7425],&quot;metro&quot;:null,&quot;blocked&quot;:false}The client should call the indexer’s/v4/compliance/geoblock endpoint\\n(or /v4/compliance/geoblock-keplr, if the user’s connected wallet is Keplr)\\nupon app launching and when the user connects to a new wallet.This will update the user&#x27;s compliance status based on the requesting IP.  To authenticate the user, sign a message with the user&#x27;s private key, and send the signed message as part of the payload. See sample implementation.\",\"title\":\"/v4/geo\",\"titles\":[\"Compliance\",\"Geo-Blocking Implementation\"]},{\"href\":\"/interaction/integration/integration-compliance#v4screen\",\"html\":\"<p>The client can query the compliant status of the user by calling the indexer’s <code>/v4/screen</code> endpoint:</p><pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><s